m. He was also noted as a poet, many of the Psalms being attributed to him. The Hebrew derivation of the name is uncertain; it is said by some to represent a nursery word meaning ‘darling’. It is a very popular Jewish name, but is almost equally common among Gentiles in the English-speaking world. It is particularly common in Wales and Scotland, having been borne by the patron saint of Wales (  see  Dewi   ) and by two medieval kings of Scotland."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"David de Annadio was born in 1323, in Sauchie, Clackmannanshire, Scotland, United Kingdom as the son of Henry De Annadio Sheriff of Clackmannanshire and Lady Henry de Annadio. He had at least 1 son with Isobel Galbraith."},"et":{"1323–":"1323–Surnud","1323–Male":"1323–Surnud","1330–1390":"1330–1390","1350–1401":"1350–1401","–1350":"–1350","1295–Female":"1295–Surnud","1401":"1401","1323":"1323","1330":"1330","1350":"1350","1295":"1295","1390":"1390","Sauchie, Clackmannanshire, Scotland":"Sauchie, Clackmannanshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1323–":"1323–Kuollut","1323–Male":"1323–Kuollut","1330–1390":"1330–1390","1350–1401":"1350–1401","–1350":"–1350","1295–Female":"1295–Kuollut","1401":"1401","1323":"1323","1330":"1330","1350":"1350","1295":"1295","1390":"1390","Sauchie, Clackmannanshire, Scotland":"Sauchie, Clackmannanshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"1323–":"1323–Décédé","1323–Male":"1323–Décédé","1330–1390":"1330–1390","1350–1401":"1350–1401","–1350":"–1350","1295–Female":"1295–Décédée","1401":"1401","1323":"1323","1330":"1330","1350":"1350","1295":"1295","1390":"1390","Sauchie, Clackmannanshire, Scotland":"Sauchie, Clackmannanshire, Écosse","lifeSummary":"David de Annadio est né en 1323, à Sauchie, Clackmannanshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni, fils de Henry De Annadio Sheriff of Clackmannanshire et Lady Henry de Annadio. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Isobel Galbraith."},"de":{"1323–":"1323–Verstorben","1323–Male":"1323–Verstorben","1330–1390":"1330–1390","1350–1401":"1350–1401","–1350":"–1350","1295–Female":"1295